sentence: Crude oil futures down 1.5 % after U.S. supply report .
https://www.investing.com/news/commodities-news/crude-oil-futures-down-1.5-after-u.s.-supply-report-246682 .

Investing.com - Crude oil futures added to losses during U.S. morning hours on Wednesday , re-approaching a four-month low despite the release of U.S. government data which showed oil supplies fell unexpectedly last week .
On the New York Mercantile Exchange , light sweet crude futures for delivery in June traded at USD87 .76 a barrel during U.S. morning trade , down 1.4 % on the day .
Prices traded at USD88 .11 a barrel prior to the release of the supply data .
New York-traded oil prices fell by as much as 1.8 % earlier in the session to hit a daily low of USD87 .47 a barrel .
Nymex oil futures fell to USD86 .41 a barrel on Tuesday , the weakest level since December 17 .

The U.S. Energy Information Administration said in its weekly report that U.S. crude oil inventories fell by 1.2 million barrels in the week ended April 12 , confounding expectations for an increase of 1.4 million barrels .
Total U.S. crude oil inventories stood at 387.6 million barrels as of last week .
Despite the bullish supply withdrawal , it came in below the 6.6 million barrel decline reported by the American Petroleum Institute on Tuesday .
The report also showed that total motor gasoline inventories decreased by 0.6 million barrels , compared to expectations for a decline of 0.8 million barrels .
The U.S. is the world 's biggest oil consuming country , responsible for almost 22 % of global oil demand .
Oil prices were down sharply earlier in the session amid concerns over the global economic outlook and its impact on future oil demand .
On Tuesday , the International Monetary Fund cut its 2013 forecast for global growth to 3.3 % , down from its January projection of 3.5 % .
It also trimmed its 2014 forecast to 4.0 % from 4.1 % .
The growth projection for China , the world 's second largest energy consumer , was trimmed to 8 % from 8.2 % , while the growth outlook for the U.S. was lowered to 1.9 % from 2 % .

Elsewhere , on the ICE Futures Exchange , Brent oil futures for June delivery was down 1.4 % to trade at USD98 .44 a barrel , with the spread between the Brent and crude contracts standing at USD10 .68 a barrel .
London-traded Brent futures fell to a nine-month low of USD98 .02 a barrel on Tuesday , amid growing concerns over the euro zone 's economic outlook .
The IMF said Tuesday the euro zone remains the weakest part of the global economy .
The 17 countries using the euro accounted for about 12 % of world demand last year .
